tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE ai_performance (
    algorithm_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    algorithm_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    performance_metric VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    accuracy FLOAT NOT NULL,
    training_time FLOAT NOT NULL,
    evaluation_time FLOAT NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE AI_Algorithms (
    algorithm_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    algorithm_name VARCHAR(255),
    accuracy DECIMAL,
    performance_metric VARCHAR(50),
    last_updated TIMESTAMP
);

CREATE TABLE Model_Results (
    result_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    algorithm_id INT,
    dataset_id INT,
    result_value DECIMAL,
    result_date DATE,
    FOREIGN KEY (algorithm_id) REFERENCES AI_Algorithms (algorithm_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (dataset_id) REFERENCES Datasets (dataset_id)
);

CREATE TABLE algorithm_tests (
  test_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  algorithm_id INT,
  test_date DATE,
  test_result VARCHAR,
  FOREIGN KEY (algorithm_id) REFERENCES ai_algorithms (algorithm_id)
);

CREATE TABLE model_parameters (
  parameter_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  algorithm_id INT,
  hyperparameter VARCHAR,
  value FLOAT,
  FOREIGN KEY (algorithm_id) REFERENCES ai_algorithms (algorithm_id)
);

CREATE TABLE execution_logs (
  log_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  algorithm_id INT,
  execution_date TIMESTAMP,
  status VARCHAR,
  FOREIGN KEY (algorithm_id) REFERENCES ai_algorithms (algorithm_id)
);

CREATE TABLE algorithm_results (
    result_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    algorithm_id INT,
    result_value FLOAT,
    result_date TIMESTAMP,
    FOREIGN KEY (algorithm_id) REFERENCES ai_algorithms(algorithm_id)
);

CREATE TABLE model_training (
    training_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    algorithm_id INT,
    training_date TIMESTAMP,
    training_duration INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (algorithm_id) REFERENCES ai_algorithms(algorithm_id)
);

CREATE TABLE hyperparameters (
    hyperparam_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    algorithm_id INT,
    hyperparam_name VARCHAR(255),
    hyperparam_value FLOAT,
    FOREIGN KEY (algorithm_id) REFERENCES ai_algorithms(algorithm_id)
);

CREATE TABLE model_accuracy (
    accuracy_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    algorithm_id INT,
    accuracy_value FLOAT,
    evaluation_date TIMESTAMP,
    FOREIGN KEY (algorithm_id) REFERENCES ai_algorithms(algorithm_id)
);
